betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Just chop down a few trees for right now, you'll need quite a bit of wood to help you get started.

While you're at it, get some saplings and re-plant the trees. #TeamTrees!

Seems pretty easy, just some dirt.

(Very good quest reward, I know.)

You need some gravel to make some flint for some basic tools. Search around for some.

Flint §cdoes not §0§fnaturally drop, and needs to be crafted. Clicking on an item in the quest book will show its crafting recipe.

You need some basic tools to get started, GregTech tools are primarily used during the whole pack. Start out now with a simple flint pickaxe to mine and a sword to kill some enemies at night.

§9Note that GregTech shows several recipes due to it being part of the same crafting ID. For the most part, it can be ignored, most of the tools are made the same way.
Make a crafting table. Pretty necessary if you ask me.
Just some basic building blocks for you to use.
Some extra tools which could help you.
Go mine some stone, you'll need a bit.

Obviously, furnaces are pretty helpful in the making of ingots. And, well, you obviously need ingots. Obviously.

It's also... a lot... of cobblestone... sorry not sorry
Yep. There's no stone tools. You'll be stuck with at best iron until a lot later on. Sorry?

Veins are generally very large and rare in here with the ocassional ore. Along some of your cobblestone mining, you may have noticed some spots on the surface. They're generally right above one of these huge ore veins. JEI will tell you where these veins spawn, and yes, some of them do spawn in only space!
No charcoal, not yet. Charcoal is made inside the coke oven later on.

Make some okay(-ish) food through your furnace. You should know what to do, right?

§5§5§4§3§5...right?

What's the difference between cobblestone and stone? I don't know, one looks a little more in shambles than the other. Anyway, get yourself some stone. Good for some GT tools.

Also looks pretty okay-ish for some building blocks.

A mortar makes life easier for you with flint. Like the flint pickaxe, it shows multiple recipes, but the middle ingots can just be replaces with (almost) any GT material and work, including flint.

§3After this quest, the quests will start saying "Darmstadium," it will be the exact same as this though, just with the flexability to do which ever material you want.§3§3§m I'm also incredibly lazy, its getting tiring to make the tool every single time.

Just a challenge. See if you could do it!

§6Not required for progression.
Will be helpful later on, better to make some now while you have a bit of stone on hand.
Get some seeds to plant, gonna be helpful for that nutrition you gotta keep up.

A boatload of wood to make a boatload of boat-- you know what, i'll just stop. Just a challenge for you to do made easier by your nifty new axe.

§6Not required, but can be helpful later on.

Just a challenge, made a little bit easier by your new shovel.

§6Not required for progression, but could be helpful.

§§§lI AM NOT A MORON!

§rI mean, uh, get yourself some wheat!

Making bread is not the same, you gotta do several processes before you can get that delicious bread.

§6Note that some parts probably can't be done right now, progress on for now.

While there are other veins which give you iron, one of the easiest ones to find will give you magnetite, an ore which can be smelted into iron. Look for the pieces on the surface to help you find a vein.

As a bonus, this vein also gives vanadium magnetite, an important ore for later on, and gold. Also gives a slight bit of normal iron ore.

§nIt is §b§nHIGHLY§b§n§n§r§n recommended you mark down any vein you come across with JourneyMap, the default key is "J"

There are several other sources of iron, such as yellow & brown limonite or banded iron. They all give just about the same thing, iron ingots. Where these veins differ however is that they are much more dense but much rarer.

This is the steam tier, where the "real fun" begins.

§4Be prepared to lose your whole life to this, seriously. GregTech is a vast mod when combined with Shadows Of Greg. You will spend hours on this part alone, hours on every voltage tier.
Make yourself some iron by throwing that ore into a furnace.
This quest leads to other veins which may be required for steam.

Copper Ore is also quite important for numerous things.

Chalcopyrite Veins are probably your best bet, as they also give some iron.
You can get some gold ore by processing the gold ore (duh)
Tin is quite an important ore. Best find yourself a vein right now.

Another source of copper, except this one is very deep and rare. But is almost exclusively copper, all the way through.

§7§6Also note that there ARE NO surface indicators of this vein. May be very difficult to find!

Tetrahedrite is another source of copper. This vein is almost excusively copper.

Is also a good source of stibnite, a very important ore later on. However, this ore cannot be processed right now.

Also only spawns in mountains.

Bronze is a really important material for making steam machines.

Bronze for now can be made by crushing down copper and tin into their dust forms, then recombining them in a 3 copper to 1 tin ratio in a crafting grid. The result is bronze dust, which can then be smelted into bronze.

§nThis is the only way to make bronze for a little while, and it is slightly innefficient. Try to change over to a different way later on!

Gregtech has a whole host of tools that you'll need, like the hammer and wrench. Remember that all of these can be made with different materials, however, your best option right now is iron. (Bronze is weaker.)

The first one you'll need is the hammer for the creation of plates.
Bronze isn't good on its own, you'll need to make it into plates!
Iron plates are necessary for numerous items, including other GT tools.
The wrench is vital to many recipes! Again, its best to make this out of iron for now.
Make yourself a file. Gonna come in handy for rods!
You're gonna need a few of these... for more GT tools!
Bronze rods will be pretty good for some Gregtech machines and multiblocks later on.
Some tin will be necessary for bronze, some more tin for some other stuff.
Copper is a necessary material for bronze, as well as some other stuff.
A saw is helpful for making wood more efficiently.
Who knew that a screw could drive? I don't know, but regardless, you'll need a screwdriver.
A crowbar will remove covers from machines via a simple right click; not helpful to you for a little while but will be helpful so you won't have to break machines.
These will be helpful for the creation of some items, like buckets.
The very start of your journey.
Goes over the Steam part of GregTech
